  • Classes in fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.hioa.models.vars used by fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.examples.hioa_with_vh 
    Class and Description
    StaticVariableDescriptor
    The class StaticVariableDescriptor contains all of the static information related to a HIOA model variable.
    Value
    The class Value defines a placeholder for the values of atomic HIOA models with a history mechanism that memorise immediately preceding values within a predefined time window.
    VariableSource
    The class VariableSource describes exported variables of submodels either to define the connections among submodels when creating a coupled model or to define how a coupled model reexports the exported variables of its submodels.

  • Classes in fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.hioa.models.vars used by fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.hioa.models.vars 
    Class and Description
    DerivableValue
    The class DerivableValue augments the superclass Value with the first derivative of the signal is known.
    StaticVariableDescriptor
    The class StaticVariableDescriptor contains all of the static information related to a HIOA model variable.
    TimedValueI
    The interface TimedValue specifies that implementing classes can return an associated Time object.
    Value
    The class Value defines a placeholder for the values of atomic HIOA models with a history mechanism that memorise immediately preceding values within a predefined time window.
    VariableDescriptor
    The class VariableDescriptor extends the class StaticVariableDescriptor with dynamic information about variables: the owner model and the Java field that defines the variable in the owner model.
    VariableSink
    The class VariableSink describes how imported variables are used in a model i.e., either a variable directly imported by an atomic model or a variable imported by a coupled model and then reimported by a submodel; note that in a coupled model, a single imported variable can be reimported by many submodels possibly using different names and types.
    VariableSource
    The class VariableSource describes exported variables of submodels either to define the connections among submodels when creating a coupled model or to define how a coupled model reexports the exported variables of its submodels.
    VariableVisibility
    The enumeration VariableVisibility defines the different possibilities for the visibility of variables in HIOA models: internal, exported or imported.
